The ability for a user (or a group of users) to insert a personal label for all confluence users or specific groups of users into a page/blogpost would simplify personalising a confluence site. The idea is that editor or an approver adds a my:somelabel for an entire user group to a page/blogpost and each user in that group can then remove it at his or her convenience.

It would be possible to use contentbylabel to display a list of pages or news items so that each user can then remove the label from the item to remove it from the listing he or she sees (mark it as read, if you will). To simplify matters, some sort of remove-label:my:somelabel -macro could be included in the item content for one click removal.

