Our [instructions for the Widget Macro|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Widget+Macro?showComments=true&showCommentArea=true#addcomment] suggest right-clicking the URLs available in the [Google Gadgets gallery|http://www.google.com/ig/directory?synd=open].

It seems like the hostname Google uses with those has changed since the \{widget\} macro was introduced.  This URL (copied from Google) doesn't work:

{code}
http://fusion.google.com/ig/add?synd=open&source=ggyp&moduleurl=http://hosting.gmodules.com/ig/gadgets/file/112581010116074801021/turtle.xml
{code}

Using this with the \{widget\} macro results in nothing but an icon and a link.  Replacing "fusion.google.com" with "www.google.com" immediately allows the widget to load, as in:

{code}
http://www.google.com/ig/add?synd=open&source=ggyp&moduleurl=http://hosting.gmodules.com/ig/gadgets/file/112581010116074801021/turtle.xml
{code}

Ideally, more robust recognition of Google Gadget URLs would be great, at a minimum the new hostname needs to be recognized (or our documentation needs to be updated).

The problem behavior is there in 3.0.0_01 and 3.1m2.

